Emre Can PHOTO:AFP German midfielder Emre Can has signed for Juventus on a four-year deal, the Turin club announced on Thursday. The 24-year-old spent four years at Liverpool but will be a free agent on July 1 when his contract at the Merseyside club expires. He completed his medical in Turin on Thursday. Juventus have won seven straight Serie A titles. Can rejected the offer of a new contract from beaten Champions League finalists Liverpool months ago amid speculation of his move to the Italian giants. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .